May your headphones snag on every door handle.
%
May your chair produce a sound similar to a fart, 
but only once, such that you cannot repoduce it 
to prove that it was just the chair.
%
May both sides of your pillow be warm.
%
May every sock you wear be slightly rotated, 
just enough for it to be uncomfortable.
%
May you forever feel your cell phone 
vibrating in the pocket it's not even in.
%
May you always get up from your computer 
with your headphones still attached.
%
May your five year old neighber have 
violin lessons during all of your hangovers.
%
May your cookie always be slightly too large 
to fit in your glass of milk.
%
May your tea be too hot when you receive it, 
and too cold by the time you remember it's there.
%
May you always step in a wet spot after putting on fresh socks.
%
May every guitar pick you use fall into the soundhole.
%
May your article load that extra little bit 
as you are about to click a link so that you 
click on an advertisement instead.
%
May the chocolate chips in your cookies always turn out to be raisins.
%
May the pin of the bathroom stall never reach the lock to close the door.
%
May your spoon always slip and sink under the hot soup you eat.
%
May your mother come talk to you, 
and then leave your door slightly ajar, 
so that you have to get up and close it.
%
May every "empty" parking space you see in the distance 
actually contain a motorcycle.
%
May you have your laptop charge overnight without 
noticing the cord isn't plugged into the wall.
%
May all your Facebook notifications be game invites.
%
May you always choose the slowest line.
%
I'd agree with you, but then we'd both be wrong.
%
You have a face for radio, and a voice for silent film.
%
I bet you couldn't pour water out of a boot if the instructions were printed on the heel
%
May the fleas of a thousand camels infest your armpits.
%
May the florecent lights always make you appear sick.
%
May the white-noise generator in your office be just noticeably loud.
%
May you always start talking at the same time as the other person on a conference call
